g.text: Exercise 8: Data Visualization
In this exercise you generate interactive views to visualize data, add a slider to filter the data, and change the colors in the graphs. At the end you
combine the graphs into an interactive composite view.
Use the data from first output port and assign a color to the customers based on their newsletter subscription
Build a scatter plot to show the relationship between the total purchase amount in the year 2019 and in the years before
(optional) Create an interactive range slider to filter the data shown in the scatter plot by the birth year of a customer
Visualize the customer data in an interactive table (Table View node)
Create a stacked area chart to
show the development of the total purchase amount over time for each transaction type
(optional)
Convert the values in the column basket size from integer to string for the data of the lowest output port
b)
(optional) Build a bar chart to show the number of products per order for the different transaction types
(optional) Change the colors of the bars and the stacked areas
Extract the column headers from the middle or bottom output of the metanode
Transpose the table with the column headers
Assign your preferred colors to the transaction types in the resulting "Column
Header" column
Use the colored table as the optional input for the Bar Chart and Stacked Area
Chart nodes
Top: Data aggregated by customer ID
Middle: Data aggregated by year, quarter, and type
Bottom: Data aggregated by basket size and type
Transform and
aggregate data
